Defendant Donovan C Koeberl in court with attorney Matthew Huppertz.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Huppertz makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  
The Court Orders the Following: Count #1.  
Withheld Sentence: (2 days credit if revoked)
Term of Probation: 2 Years
Early release from Probation after 18 months if agent deems appropriate;
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Disclose to any physician in writing your drug history/dependency signed by your physician and provide a copy to your Agent. 
Sign Medical Release for Agent;
Maintain/Obtain employment;
Condition Time: 30 days Huber with NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - To commence Monday 1/11/2016 @ 6:00 pm.  Last 20 days of the 30 days are STAYED - to be used at the Agents discretion
COSTS:  $268.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Surcharge: $250.00  to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.  
Expunction is conditionally granted upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.
